A recent survey in urban Shanghai revealed high obesity rates in both adults and children, mirroring developed countries.
Experts warn of health risks like cardiovascular disease due to poor lifestyle choices.
Beijing's overweight population attributes their condition to lack of exercise and high-fat diets.
The government aims to reduce obesity rates by promoting healthier habits.
In Kuwait, hypnotherapy has shown success in treating obesity.
In the UAE, diabetes rates are rising due to obesity.
Education on balanced diets and preventive measures are crucial to combat these health issues.
